description.code:
err = $error
if (err) 
  printf "Got error %d (%s)\n", err, errmsg(err);
endif

description.para:
Returns the inverse hyperbolic cosine of x
(positive solution). x should be greater than 1;
otherwise, NA is returned.

description.code:
matrix M = {1,2;2,1;4,1}
colnames(M, "Col1 Col2")
print M

li.para:
If the i-th eigenvalue is real, the
i-th column of U will contain the
corresponding eigenvector;

description.para:
The matrix types gretl checks for are: identity; diagonal;
symmetric and positive definite; symmetric but not positive
definite; and triangular.

description.code:
a = {1,2,3;3,4,5}
find = {1,3,4}
subst = {-1,-8, 0}
b = replace(a, find, subst)
print a b

